---
title: Citrusy Tex-Mex Chicken with Spiced Veggie Jumble & Lime Crema
description: Juicy pork tenderloin loves a little something sweet, and sweetness pairs beautifully with a little spicy heat! Lucky you—tonight’s dinner has it all. Succulent pork is seasoned with our Southwest Spice Blend, seared, then roasted to perfection beside a colorful array of sweet potatoes, green bell pepper, and red onion. Top the pork with a citrusy Tex-Mex sauce made with fresh orange and lime juice, and drizzle your plate with cool, tangy lime crema just before serving. Cheers to perfect pairings!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/citrusy-tex-mex-pork-tenderloin-eece9be4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65395fd29ac0a520c65e3bfb.pdf
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 490 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 44 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 640 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/citrusy-tex-mex-chicken-65395fd29ac0a520c65e3bfb
servings: 2
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and
dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{1}(diced) into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and slice @red onion{1}(peeled and sliced) into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(thinly sliced) into strips. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Halve @orange{1}.

Toss sweet potato, onion, and bell pepper on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{1%tsp}, half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1/2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with remaining Southwest Spice Blend, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a second baking sheet. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in pork for chicken. Cook 4-8 minutes per side for searing, then roast until cooked through.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Roast chicken on middle rack until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

While chicken and veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of lime zest.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

About 5 minutes before chicken and veggies are done, heat pan used for chicken over
medium-high heat. Stir in half the @Tex-Mex Paste{1/2%unit} (all for 4 servings), juice from orange halves, and a squeeze of lime juice. Bring to a simmer and cook until
sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and combined.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken and veggie jumble between plates. Spoon Tex-Mex sauce over chicken.
Drizzle crema over everything and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> For larger servings, use 2 tbsp Tex-Mex paste and 2 tbsp butter, and 2 cups sour cream.